from george f krumin subject re vandalizing the sky nicho greg stewart-nicholl write in george f krumin write i wa suggest that the minority of professional and amateur astronomer have the right to a dark unclutter night sky sorry you have a wish for an unclutter night sky but it be a right when you get down to it you actually have no right that the majority have agree to give you and them in the proces it a common misconception that be bear somehow endow you with right to thi that and the other sadly thi be not true now if you want to talk about the responsibility that should go with the power to clutter the night sky then that a different matter greg nicholl vidi nicho or vicus nicho veni according to thi reason there be no right at least none that i can think of let see do i have a right to unpolluted air no because the majority drive car and use good that create air pollution in the manufacture proces do i have the right to clean water i gues not by the same reason i could go on with these example for a long time look at nazi germany because of the majority jew homosexual black and other that be different have no right in fact they be terrorize imprison and slaughter in thi country do black have the right to be free from slavery i gues not because the majority say that slavery wa good for them i think that a right ha a moral imperative if a law impose by the majority be immoral one should not follow it in fact one should do everything in power to stop it of course that do mean that i would lose all common sense to break the law just because i think it wa immoral i pay my federal income tax even though i be morally oppose to the government take my money and spend it on weapon of ma destruction and terrorism thi be precisely the point i be try to make we should persude person by logic point out that it be in their self-interest to let all have equal right in all aspect of life include adequate house food and medical care i just happen to think that for a full life